# CLAUDE.md — Android (Compose + MVI + Koin)

## Always apply these skills

- android-presentation-mvi
- android-compose-ui
- android-data-layer
- android-error-handling
- android-di-koin
- android-coroutines-flow
- android-navigation
- android-testing

## Module rules

- `feature` modules depend on `core:domain` only — never on `core:data` or other feature modules
- `core:data` depends on `core:domain`
- `app` assembles all DI modules and owns the nav host

## Patterns to follow

- Every screen: `State` + `Action` + `Event` in a sealed hierarchy
- ViewModel exposes `StateFlow<State>` and `fun onAction(Action)`
- Navigation events via `Channel`, collected in root composable with `LaunchedEffect`
- Repositories return `Result<T, DataError>` — never throw across boundaries
- Tests use `FakeRepository` — no Mockito or MockK

## Do not

- Add business logic inside `@Composable` functions
- Use `LiveData` — `StateFlow` only
- Hardcode strings — all user-facing text in `strings.xml` via `UiText`
- Use `GlobalScope`
